>
  <p>The very famous city of Cannes is known all over the world for its Film Festival. On the famous Croisette, you will be dazzled by the luxury hotels, the shops, the Art Deco buildings on one side and the sandy beaches on the sea side.</p>
  <p>The historical district of Le Suquet awaits you next to the old port. From the top of the old town, you will have a breathtaking view of the Islands and the Croisette.</p>
  <p>Facing this lively city, you will find peace within 15 minutes by boat on the Lérins Islands. The island of Sainte Marguerite has kept its wild character. At Fort Royal, you rediscover the legend of the Iron Mask.</p>
  <p>Its little neighbor, the Island of Saint-Honorat, is privately owned by Cistercian monks. The monks produce a famous wine as well as liquors and olive oil.</p>
